  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> a pot with a lid with 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [350ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676308041752-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676308041752-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676308041752-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676308041752-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676308041752-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to char</p><p>Once done, transfer to a bowl and set aside for later (reserve the pan!) –<strong> </strong>this is your<strong> charred corn</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676308092653-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676308092653-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676308092653-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676308092653-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676308092653-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the corn is charring, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Dissolve your<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> chipotle stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676308101892-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676308101892-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676308101892-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676308101892-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676308101892-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until lightly golden</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676308113679-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676308113679-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676308113679-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676308113679-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676308113679-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has slightly softened, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground coriander</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min until fragrant, then add the <strong>chipotle stock</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5-7 min or until thickened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676308134129-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676308134129-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676308134129-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676308134129-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676308134129-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>remaining ground smoked paprika</strong>,<strong> remaining</strong> <strong>ground coriander</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> black pepper</strong> in a shallow bowl</p><p>Add your<strong> haddock bites </strong>to the bowl and give everything a good mix up until fully coated in the spices – these are your <strong>spiced haddock bites</strong></p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676308143210-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676308143210-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676308143210-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676308143210-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676308143210-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, top with the <strong>spiced haddock bites </strong>and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further or until the fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>Mexican-style spiced haddock stew</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Add the <strong>charred corn</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>to the cooked rice<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>charred corn rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676308153008-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676308153008-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676308153008-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676308153008-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676308153008-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Mexican-style spiced haddock stew</strong> with the <strong>charred corn rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped coriander</strong> and a pinch of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
